2.caption: 1966 East–West Pro Bowl
2.description: The 1966 Pro Bowl was the National Football League's sixteenth annual all-star game which featured the outstanding performers from the 1965 season. The game was played on January 16, 1966, at the Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum in Los Angeles in front of a crowd of 60,124.
2.inspected:Co-MVPs: Jim Brown (Cleveland Browns), Dale Meinert (St. Louis Cardinals)
